    <p> Well, when I think of this hostel I only think of words like: corner, dirty, spotted, neglected and just Pfui. </p>
    <p> I had booked the Balmain Backpacker's Hostel in Sydney in Sydney for my first 6 nights because it was cheap and a little bit of the center. The problems with the hostel started before I was there. Since everything took a little longer at the airport, I tried to reach the hostel by phone to make sure that I still come in because the reception is only occupied until 5 p.m. Of course I couldn't reach anyone except that. So I just drove there, hoping that someone is already leaving me in. </p>
    <p> A friendly young man also opened the door to me and also knew about my arrival. After we went through the nothing that was said, it became strange for the first time. The gear behind the door ended in a garage. There were several vehicles, a washing machine two autmats and a group of really rancid chairs around an even more rancid table. Smiling, the young man told me that this was one of the lounges. I still hoped that it would be better. Unfortunately it wasn't. </p>
