    <p> In the middle of the garage, a staircase went up to the first floor, in which one of the two kitchens was located. This did not look really inviting and was also full of people. We then went on to the second floor, where there are some guest rooms and the second kitchen. This was actually no longer usable. The oven was missing completely and most of the shelves were missing. The seating furniture that stood in front of the kitchenette looked like they had been brought to bulky waste 3 times and unloaded here again. Sit through, with holes and slots. The wooden floor has also been wet several times because it had risen in some places like a sponge. </p>
    <p> It then continued over a terrace, with dirty and unkempt garden furniture, to another stairwell. On the next floor, he showed me other wicked rooms, such as bathrooms, toilets, a really corner ironing board and also the room where I should sleep for the next 6 nights. The room was even reasonably clean. But so small that there was no space for decent storage space. So I just had to put my things on the floor. In addition, there was no way for me to close my valuables properly. </p>
