    <p> The door could only be opened inwards. So you always have to push yourself past one of the beds when leaving the room. The window went out to the main street and was open all the time, otherwise we would braise in our own juice. Of course there is no air conditioning. The upper end of the wall to the hallway is made of glass stones. Thus, the room is heavily illuminated at night, whenever someone turns the door to the hallway and triggers the motion detector for light. Oh and the double -stick bed has no ladder and also wiggled suspiciously. </p>
    <p> The bathroom was so dirty and disgusting that I taught myself how to use a bathroom including showering without touching anything. The sagrotan bottle became my best friend there. The sink wobbled. The amatur was only loose in the bracket. The door of the shower cubicle had been replaced by a poorly attached shower curtain. The tiles themselves did not look that old yet, but the joints were so dirty that you don't get them clean without a hammer and chisel. </p>
