    <p> In the evening it smelled suspiciously of hemp in the garage in the garage and as much as that could be really bad. I was glad that I hadn't paid for every 6 nights. It quickly became clear to me that I won't be able to endure it for a very long time. The next day I went to management to address the problems. The lady took note of it all, but looked at me as if nothing would change anyway. </p>
    <p> I decided to stay a second night because the next day I was invited to Newcastle for a trial day at an agency. I still had to pay for 3 nights because Balmain Backpacker's Hostel had to be booked at least 3 nights. I only regret the German girl, which was in a room with me. She thought similarly to me, but had decided to stay there all booked nights. I hope that she found something better afterwards. </p>
